  "_doc": "Innistrad: Crimson Vow (VOW) booster recipe. The `draft` block is generated by scripts/gen-booster-contents.mjs from data/_collation-facts/vow.json (source: The Collation Project, lethe.xyz/mtg/collation) — do not hand-edit it unless you also remove its facts source. The `collector` block is hand-authored from Wizards' official \"Collecting Innistrad: Crimson Vow\" article (magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-innistrad-crimson-vow-2021-10-28) and the matching Product Overview; the 12-slot structure is verbatim from the article. VOW is a 2021 set (pre-Play Booster) so there is NO play booster. Treatment splits model the article: 5 rares/mythics (2 foil), 10 traditional foils, 8 special-treatment cards, 1–3 Dracula series, 2–3 extended-art, 2–6 showcase incl. eternal-night land, 0–2 borderless. Dracula-series cards (Scryfall promo_types draculaseries, inverted frame) have no dedicated filter in data/filters.json, so the Dracula slots are approximated via the `showcase` Booster-Fun pool; per the article the guaranteed non-foil Dracula is uncommon just over half the time and rare/mythic otherwise, and the foil Dracula odds are ~14% uncommon / ~11% rare-or-mythic. Commander rares/mythics come from the Crimson Vow Commander set (voc). Set composition: 100C / 83U / 64R / 20M. 'authoritative' so the date heuristic doesn't fabricate a play booster.",
